Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{400%g} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Pop the chunks onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and seeded) and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips, then chop into roughly 1cm pieces. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(thinly sliced).

Finely chop @parsley{10%g}(finely chopped). Thinly slice @scallion{1}(thinly sliced). Halve the @cherry tomatoes{125%g}(halved). Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(grated) (or use a garlic press).

Stir together the @aioli{1%sachet}, half the parsley and half the garlic in a #small bowl{}. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium heat.

Add the onions. Cook, stirring often, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @balsamic vinegar{1%sachet} and @sugar{1%tsp} (double for 4p). Season with salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until dark golden brown, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat. Transfer the onions to another small bowl and set aside. Carefully wipe pan clean.

Heat the same pan with another drizzle of oil over medium-high heat.

When hot, add the pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @chorizo{100%g} and remaining garlic. Cook the chorizo for ~{3-4%minutes}, until browned. Season with salt and pepper.

Add roasted potatoes, tomatoes, half the scallions and remaining parsley to the pan with chorizo. Stir together.

Divide hash between bowls and top with caramelised onions.

Dollop with parsley aioli and sprinkle remaining scallions over the top.